Struggling young Feral hefted the bulky pack to her still searing back and settled it into place. Biting back a groan as she felt the straps of it bite into her shoulders. With sheer stubborness she willed her legs to move as she took up a plodding pace behind him. Several feet behind him. And so it went for nearly 16 hours. They traveled relentlessly through Nektulos forest, then into the hills of east commons. <br>
Sweat burned her eyes as she trudged relentlessly behind him. She'd be damned if she'd beg for a break. Temper simmered into pure unadultered hatred and with it came the much needed strenght she would need to continue the journey. <br>
By night fall she moved in auto. Her muscles long since numbed to the pain. Her mind dazed in fatigue. So immersed in her own thoughts that it was'nt until she slammed into his back with a resounding thud that sent her falling to her backside that she realized he had finally stopped. &quot;We'll make camp here. Set that down and gather fire wood.&quot; <br>
Feral shot a glare at him as she let the pack fall to the ground and spun about. Vowing to one day make him pay. She set off to gather fire wood. She knew as sure as the sun would rise in but a few hours, that her muscles would soon be screaming in agony.... <br>
<br>
